 the authors' coverage here showcases the diversity of social and noncriminal deviance. Deviance Management allows for a more thorough understanding of strategies typically used by normalization movements to destigmatize behaviors and identities while contributing to the study of social movements and intra-movement conflict.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aDeviant behaviorzUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh  abeing stigmatized as deviant.  adestigmatize behaviors and identities.  adiversity of social and noncriminal deviance.  adrifters.  aexamination of social deviant label.  ahigh tension religious groups.  algbtq groups.  aparanormal subcultures.  arecreational drug and alcohol users.  asocial movements and intra movement conflict.  asociology of deviance.  astigma of being labeled socially deviant.  awhite power movements.1 aBaker, Joseph O., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics, Law & Social Sciences 2019 ENGz978311061013008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2019z9783110606485oZDB-23-DSW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCA Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065207908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311066763940uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520973121zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520973121423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520973121.jpg  a978-3-11-061013-0  EBOO